Part 1: The Environment & System Logic

    Libraries

        dotenv (load_dotenv): A configuration utility. It is used to securely load hidden environment
                              variables from a local .env file into the computer's temporary memory,
                              preventing API keys from being hardcoded in plain text.

        os: A system-level library. It is used specifically via os.getenv() to retrieve the API key that
            load_dotenv just placed into the system's memory.

    Variables

        system_prompt: A static string variable. It contains the highly detailed behavioral constraints,
                       historical context, and persona instructions that force the underlying AI to act
                       strictly as Sir Isaac Newton.

Part 2: The LangChain Orchestration (The Engine)

    LangChain is the framework used to chain different AI components together so they operate as a single machine.

    Classes & Modules

        ChatGoogleGenerativeAI: The specific communication bridge. It connects the Python script directly
                                to Google's Gemini models.

        ChatPromptTemplate: A dynamic text blueprint. It structures the conversation exactly how the AI needs
                            to read it, separating the hidden system instructions, the historical context,
                            and the newest user input.

        MessagesPlaceholder: A dynamic injection point. It acts as a designated empty space inside the
                             ChatPromptTemplate where the entire history of the conversation will be dynamically
                             inserted before being sent to the AI.

        HumanMessage & AIMessage: Standardized data wrappers. LangChain requires all chat history to be categorized
                                  as either something a human said or something the AI said. These classes format the
                                  raw text into the strict structure the LLM expects.

        StrOutputParser: A formatting tool. When the AI generates a response, it often comes back as a complex
                         data object. This parser strips away the metadata and extracts only the raw, readable string text.

    The Pipeline

        chain = prompt | llm | StrOutputParser(): This is LangChain Expression Language (LCEL). It physically links the
                                                  components. It dictates that data must flow first into the prompt template,
                                                  then into the LLM, and finally through the string parser before returning to
                                                  the user.

